**Event Title:** CON - AppSec Challenge  
**Organizer:** SAINTCON, sponsored by @Sketrik & @l4wke  
**Event Description:** Participants compete to identify and fix vulnerabilities in a web application, using a cloned repository that includes several microservices written in different programming languages. Participants are allowed to utilize automated tools for assistance.  
**Event URL:** [https://saintcon.org/con-appsec-challenge/](https://saintcon.org/con-appsec-challenge/)  
**Competition Details:**
- **Start Date:** Tuesday at 12 PM
- **End Date:** Friday at 9 AM
- **Booth Hours:**
  - Tuesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Wednesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Friday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM
- **Participation Requirements:** 
  - Basic programming knowledge
  - Participants must clone the repo, find and fix vulnerabilities, ensure unit tests pass, and submit their code for scoring.
- **Scoring:** Vulnerabilities are scored based on their difficulty.
- **Prizes:** Awards for the highest scoters.
- **Tiebreakers:** Go to the first submission.
- **Prohibited actions:** Hacking the contest mechanics or using hardcoded solutions to bypass functionality tests.   
**Community Support:** Participants can seek assistance from the AppSec community via Discord or directly from the organizers if needed.  
**Get Started Link:** [https://appsec.saintcon.community/](https://appsec.saintcon.community/)  
**Contest Rules:**
- Only change files specified by the make-package.py file.
- File uploads must be less than 4MB, with one submission every five minutes.  
**Additional Information:** Desktop wallpaper is available for download related to the event. Participants are encouraged to join the AppSec community to smoothen their experience.  
**Image Link:** ![AppSec Challenge Splash](http://www.saintcon.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/AppSecChallengeSplash2024.png)